# Settings + Messaging Refactor Boundaries

- Keep settings defaults separate from storage ownership:
  - `src/settings/default-settings.js` owns `DEFAULT_SETTINGS`.
  - `src/settings/settings-service.js` owns `chrome.storage` access and default-safe merge/reset.
  - Tests and pure modules may import `DEFAULT_SETTINGS` without pulling `chrome.storage`.
- Keep `src/settings/index.js` as the compatibility public export surface when existing callers import settings.
- Keep `src/background/message-router.js` readable as a route table over small service calls. Move side-effect details into focused background services.
- Preserve the runtime response envelope from `service-worker.js`: `{ ok: true, data }` / `{ ok: false, error }`.
- UI, content, popup, options, and viewer callers must use `sendMessage()` from `src/messaging/index.js`; do not call `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` directly from those layers.
- Background/service ownership modules may use direct `chrome.*` APIs where they own that browser integration.
- Do not add or change message type string literals outside `MESSAGE_TYPES`.
- Settings broadcast must keep runtime update behavior for content scripts. If optimizing tab targeting later, prove that Markdown viewer tabs still receive `MESSAGE_TYPES.SETTINGS_UPDATED`.
